Common viva questions
1. What is CSS?
CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It is used to style web pages.
2. How many types of CSS are there?
Three types:
•	Inline CSS 
•	Internal CSS 
•	External CSS 
3. What is inline CSS?
CSS written directly inside an HTML tag.
4. What is internal CSS?
CSS written inside the <style> tag in the HTML file.
5. What is external CSS?
CSS written in a separate .css file.
6. Which tag links external CSS?
<link>
7. Why should both files be in the same folder?
So the HTML file can find the CSS file.
8. What does border-collapse: collapse; do?
It joins table borders into a single border.
________________________________________
Very likely practical question
Which CSS has highest priority?
Answer:
Inline CSS has the highest priority.

